===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|talent}}, from {{inh|en|ang|talente}}, borrowed from the plural of {{der|en|la|talentum||a Grecian weight; a talent of money}}, from {{der|en|grc|τάλαντον||balance, a particular weight, especially of gold, sum of money, a talent}}. Compare {{cog|goh|talenta||talent}}. Later senses from {{der|en|fro|talent||a talent, also will, inclination, desire}}.

